creator: Onde OU
descriptionHtml:
Sandbox Passenger is an app for testing third-party booking modules integration via dispatch API.

Sandbox Passenger app is used by developers to test dispatch API using sandbox environment. These tests check how orders from third-party system are received to Onde client's dispatch panel.

The app can not be used for the purpose of exploring Onde system. This function is served by Onde Playground app available via the link below: https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.multibrains.taxi.passenger.demo

Sandbox Passenger can be used by existing clients only. Feel free to contact support@onde.app to request Onde Dispatch API documentation and get assistance with testing. Our support team will gladly provide you with access to set up company on sandbox, as well as instructions on how to generate necessary sandbox dispatch API token.
descriptionShort: Passenger app for third-party booking module integration tests via dispatch API

appDetails.recentChangesHtml: We updated the app to make trip costs transparent — all the additional fees will be shown as part of the whole sum on the screen. Also, the Romanian language added, stabilization improved and no bugs left unnoticed. Be safe on the roads!

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
Fairness, flexibility, and simplicity — these are the main principles for our new cancellation policy.
From now on, when the driver cancels an order for some reason, this order will be taken back to the list of active orders, and another driver will be able to pick it up shortly.
Goedendag, Helló, Labdien!
Our system speaks Dutch, Hungarian, and Latvian now. Be safe on the roads!

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
We have completely reworked the Customer app and created a simple and intuitive interface taking into account feedback from users from all over the world.

Now all important features are in your sight, you can find them exactly where you and millions of other users expect to see them.

The new design was created paying attention to needs of different people. You can easily read texts without glasses, and the size of buttons allows to use the app even with your gloves.
